## When shall I use CayleyNet?

CayleyNet is a Graph CNN with spectral zoom properties able to effectively operate with signals defined over graphs. Thanks to its particular spectral properties, CayleyNet is well suited for dealing with a variety of different domains (e.g. citation networks, community graphs, user/item similarity graphs...

Graph Convolutional Neural Networks with Complex Rational Spectral Filters

usage.excerpt: CayleyNet is a Graph CNN with spectral zoom properties able to effectively operate with signals defined over graphs. Thanks to its particular spectral properties, CayleyNet is well suited for dealing with a variety of different domains (e.g. citation networks, community graphs, user/item similarity graphs...). Variations of the architecture here implemented achieved state-of-the-art performance on vertex classification, community detection and matrix completion tasks.
